Name: name
Description: Description

Name: code_meaning
Description: Description of the meaning of the code value

Name: phones
Description: Lists the stored attributes of Phone objects

Name: variables
Description: A dictionary holding the extra information about user so that specific variables do not need to be held, e.g. IM, alternate phone, second address, facebook, etc.

Name: position_name
Description: The position or role of the contact. For example, it may be preferable to name "OOI Data Curator" as a contact instead of giving an individual's name, since the individual may change through time.

Name: administrative_area
Description: Any placenames that are less specific than country and more specific than city, e.g. state or province.

Name: url
Description: url for the contact

Name: base_types
Description: List of event super types

Name: description
Description: readable description of the event (not required)

Name: origin
Description: the origin of the event (content specific to subtype). Mostly a resource id

Name: origin_type
Description: the type of origin (e.g. resource type, etc) or empty

Name: sub_type
Description: A specialization of the event_type expressed by this object type (or empty)

Name: ts_created
Description: timestamp of event created in millis in UNIX epoch

Name: geospatial_latitude_limit_north
Description: specifies one or both limits, for any or all of an entity's latitude, longitude, and vertical position, with respect to a geospatial CRS

Name: geospatial_latitude_limit_south
Description: specifies the southernmost latitude

Name: geospatial_longitude_limit_west
Description: specifies the westernmost longitude (if the value is larger than the maximum longitude, the bounds fall on either side of the 18th meridian, and the enclosed area includes that meridian)

Name: geospatial_longitude_limit_east
Description: specifies the easternmost longitude (if the value is smaller than the minimum longitude, the bounds fall on either side of the 18th meridian, and the enclosed area includes that meridian)

Name: geospatial_vertical_min
Description: specifies the (numerically) minimum vertical position; if the vertical/z axis positive (geospatial_vertical_positive)is down, the minimum value will be further away from earth center than the maximum value

Name: geospatial_vertical_max
Description: specifies the (numerically) maximum vertical position; if the vertical/z axis positive (geospatial_vertical_positive) is down, the maximum value will be closer to earth center than the minimum value

Name: geospatial_geodetic_crs
Description: The geospatial  coordinate reference system, expressed as a URI (ideally a URL); incorporates both coordinate system and datum; may be geodetic horizonal, vertical, or both

Name: geospatial_vertical_crs
Description: the vertical coordinate reference system, expressed as a URI (ideally a URL); incorporates both coordinate system and datum

Name: geospatial_latitude_units
Description: specifies the units of measure for latitude

Name: geospatial_longitude_units
Description: specifies the units of measure for longitude

Name: geospatial_vertical_units
Description: specifies the units of measure for the vertical location; overrides the geospatial_vertical_crs, if those units are different

Name: geospatial_vertical_positive
Description: specifies the direction meant by more positive vertical location values; up indicates more positive values are further from earth's center

Name: geospatial_latitude
Description: specifies the latitude, longitude, and/or vertical location of an entity, with respect to a geospatial CRS

Name: geospatial_longitude
Description: specifies the longitude

Name: geospatial_horizontal_accuracy
Description: the accuracy of the lat/lon info, expressed in the same units as the lat/lon fields

Name: geospatial_vertical_location
Description: specifies a vertical position (relative to the datum, along the axis direction specified by geospatial_vertical_positive)

Name: geospatial_vertical_accuracy
Description: the accuracy of the vertical value, expressed in the same units

Name: connection_port
Description: unique identification of the port to which the deployed device is attached (let's say a CV term appropriate to the parent device)

Name: offset_x
Description: offset location of the mounted device along the Y axis of the mounting platform, with more positive offsets indicating the device is further along the positive direction of that axis and  indicating the device is at the origin of the axis (see https://confluence.oceanobservatories.org/display/CIDev/Coordinate+Systems+and+Coordinate+Transformations#CoordinateSystemsandCoordinateTransformations-MountingPosition)

Name: offset_y
Description: offset location of the mounted device along the Z axis of the mounting platform, with more positive offsets indicating the device is further along the positive direction of that axis and  indicating the device is at the origin of the axis (see https://confluence.oceanobservatories.org/display/CIDev/Coordinate+Systems+and+Coordinate+Transformations#CoordinateSystemsandCoordinateTransformations-MountingPosition)

Name: offset_z
Description: offset location of the mounted device along the X axis of the mounting platform, with more positive offsets indicating the device is further along the positive direction of that axis andd  indicating the device is at the origin of the axis (seehttps://confluence.oceanobservatories.org/display/CIDev/Coordinate+Systems+and+Coordinate+Transformations#CoordinateSystemsandCoordinateTransformations-MountingPosition)

Name: rotation_x
Description: indicates which way a device is pointing relative to its platform; specifies the rotation around the X axis (the first rotation offset) in degrees clockwise; assumes device is pointing out Z axis (see https://confluence.oceanobservatories.org/display/CIDev/Coordinate+Systems+and+Coordinate+Transformations#CoordinateSystemsandCoordinateTransformations-MountingOrientation)

Name: rotation_y
Description: indicates which way a device is pointing relative to its platform; specifies the rotation around the Y axis (the second rotation offset, after the X rotation) in degrees clockwise; assumes device is pointing out Z axis (see https://confluence.oceanobservatories.org/display/CIDev/Coordinate+Systems+and+Coordinate+Transformations#CoordinateSystemsandCoordinateTransformations-MountingOrientation)

Name: rotation_z
Description: indicates which way a device is pointing relative to its platform; specifies the rotation around the Z axis (the last rotation offset, after the X and Y rotations) in degrees clockwise; assumes device is pointing out Z axis (see https://confluence.oceanobservatories.org/display/CIDev/Coordinate+Systems+and+Coordinate+Transformations#CoordinateSystemsandCoordinateTransformations-MountingOrientation)

Name: phone_number
Description: The phone number.  phone number is assumed US if no '+' prefix exists to specify a country code

Name: phone_type
Description: The type of phone number

Name: sms
Description: Boolean that indicates if the phone number is SMS

Name: standard_name
Description: From the CF standard_names

Name: long_name
Description: a longer descriptive name

Name: ooi_short_name
Description: The 7 character code (now being expanded to >7 characters) used by OL to identify core data producs, e.g. TEMPWAT)

Name: fill_value
Description: indicates the value that codes for a missing value

Name: cdm_data_type
Description: The THREDDS data type

Name: parameter_characteristic_reports
Description: Provides information on the measurement accuracy, precision, etc.

Name: axis
Description: For CF compliance, holds X, Y, Z or T for variables holding lat, lon, depth, and time info, respectively

Name: code_reports
Description: Provide the meaning of flags, or other code lists that need description

Name: characteristic_name
Description: Name of the characteristic being reported on. Common ones include accuracy, precision, and drift

Name: value
Description: The value of the characteristic

Name: units
Description: The units associated with the value of the characteristic

Name: applicable_range_min
Description: If the value is only valid within a particular range, this gives the minimum. Must be in same units as the value.

Name: applicable_range_max
Description: If the value is only valid within a particular range, this gives the maximum. Must be in same units as the value.

Name: source
Description: Indicates the category of the source of the value, such as manufacturer, literature, etc

Name: comments
Description: Any additional important information about the characteristic

Name: start_datetime
Description: The start of the timespan

Name: end_datetime
Description: The end of the timespan

Name: name
Description: Allows the kind of datetime to be specified, in cases where more than one TemporalBounds is used in a ResourceType. For example to differentiate the planned vs actual deployment datetimes.

Name: ioos_category
Description: Selection from IOOS controlled vocabulary for parameters

Name: reference_urls
Description: List of URLs with information about the data parameter

Name: additional_attributes
Description: Holds additional attributes, especially those provided by external providers that are difficult to characterize in advance

Name: device_id
Description: the id of the device to which this position applies relative to the parent device  (usually an instrument on a platform)

Name: term_value
Description: A keyword applied to a resource

Name: vocabulary_name
Description: The name of the vocabulary or guideline from which the keyword was drawn, if applicable

Name: term_url
Description: A URL defining a term

Name: vocabulary_url
Description: a URL to the source of a controlled vocabulary

Name: user
Description: The identity of the user who has a subscription to the data product

Name: temporal_bounds
Description: The start and end datetime of the user subscription. End datetime will be null for ongoing subscriptions

Name: archive_name
Description: Name of an external repository where the data product has been submitted

Name: submission_datetime
Description: The last datetime this data product was submitted to an external repository  (timestamp, no constraints, stored)

Name: archive_url
Description: The URL of the data product within an external repository

Name: id_in_archive
Description: the Unique ID of the resource in an external repository

Name: archive_contact
Description: the contact information for the archive POC
